Georgedale, KZN. Pic: eNCA KWAZULU-NATAL - At least 45 people have died in devastating floods in KwaZulu Natal. One family has lost five members in Hammarsdale in Durban. Scores are still missing. Heavy downpours have been battering the province since the weekend, causing flash floods that have left a trail of destruction and damage to infrastructure. Premier Sihle Zikalala has visited one of the most hit areas in eThekwini. At least 45 people have died in devastating #KZNFloods. Heavy downpours have been battering the province since the weekend, causing flash floods that have left a trail of destruction. Premier Sihle Zikalala visited one of the most hit areas in eThekwini. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/d5xpzeYWd6